    "description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3008240/extras/c5b55535fc18da53e87fb11670f03d1b.poster.avif?t=1750805869\" width=614 height=200 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3008240/extras/c5b55535fc18da53e87fb11670f03d1b.webm?t=1750805869\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3008240/extras/c5b55535fc18da53e87fb11670f03d1b.mp4?t=1750805869\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br>How We Die is a deck-building roguelike game with a board game/TRPG feeling that transforms uncertain probabilities into certainties.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >The Game Becomes Reality</h2>Hic and Illec complete a TRPG scenario that summons aliens. The next day, they hear news of an alien invasion in reality. Their game master, Is, leaves only a message saying, &quot;Come to my home,&quot; before disappearing.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Pack Useful Tools in Your Bag</h2>You can't achieve anything with bare hands. Defeat enemies and gather various tools to progress to the next map and reach your destination.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Use Tools Consecutively</h2>As long as you meet the conditions, you can use tools as much as you want. Maximize your efficiency by utilizing combos to the fullest.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Enhance Your Character as You Go</h2>Dice are resources and action points. Strengthen and modify the numbers on the dice faces to increase probabilities and create better combinations.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Add Settings to Your Character</h2>Shouldn't we avoid adding alien worship beliefs to Illec? What's the harm if it increases the draw count?",
